summary: I feel like coming into Doctor Who, it was a given that Peter Capaldi is known as an amazing actor who was going to deliver...
body:
I feel like coming into Doctor Who, it was a given that Peter Capaldi is known as an amazing actor who was going to deliver amazing performances as the Doctor, and he didn’t disappoint.

I feel like, at least for me, Matt‘s acting ability was unknown coming to the show, so it was a very nice surprise for me that he turned out to be a great actor from the beginning but ended up maturing and developing in the role as seasons went on to become a truly exceptional actor. (And not just as the Doctor, he got an Emmy nomination for the Crown, which he deserved to win, in my opinion).

I’d seen Jodie in Broadchurch and knew she was a good actress, but of course the role of the Doctor is a unique one, so you never know. Almost immediately in the first episode, she proved that her acting as the Doctor was already amazing and it’s only the beginning.

That’s not to leave out David. David’s acting ability, passion, and energy he put into the Doctor literally made the Tenth Doctor’s character. I believe David is why so many people love Ten. On his own and on paper, Ten had some flaws, and without David bringing a certain charisma and charm and lovable elements to the character, he may not have been so-well loved if handled by another actor.

In my opinion, Christopher Eccleston is like Peter, in that way that he’s one of those already masterful actors who was obviously going to deliver exceptional performances as the Doctor, and he did.

summary: Voyage of the Damned - Behind the Scenes (Part 9)  Excerpts from Benjamin Cook’s interview with Kylie from DWM #390  So was...
caption:
Voyage of the Damned - Behind the Scenes (Part 9)

Excerpts from Benjamin Cook’s interview with Kylie from DWM #390

So was Kylie nervous about taking on the role? She looks like a cool lady, but DWM wonders whether there’s an inner turbulence there…?

“I was a little nervous,” she confesses. “But being amongst such wonderful actors, and playing opposite David Tennant, who’s divine, made me determined to do my absolute best.” If you were hoping for tales of behind-the-scenes bust-ups and falling-outs, you’ll be disappointed, because Kylie stresses one point: “I have to say, everyone made me feel so welcome and at ease, which made my job a whole lot easier.”

Which scene from Voyage of the Damned is Kylie most proud of?

“Um… I’m not sure which scene,” she says, perhaps wary of spoilers, “but the one that I always think of is the first one that we shot: crossing the bridge. It was a great first day as the gang, all my co-stars, were in that scene, and it felt like we were united from the beginning. I loved meeting all the other actors, and it’s amazing how you just become used to hanging out with a guy who looks like a prickly red conker!”

Thank you to anyone who shared set photos!

title: Beware the Bad Samaritan— How Many Dumb Criminals Does It Take to Be a Dumb Criminal?
body:
4 Minute Read. Bad Samaritan 2018 starring David Tennant as serial killer Cale Erendreich. Was this movie overlooked and underrated? @electricentertainment

This film got swept under the rug this year. Is it underrated and overlooked? It’s been so long since this was all buzzy and popular and since people were talking about it I’ve forgotten why I heard it wasn’t worth watching. But here I am. I ended up watching this twice because it was so unmemorable the first time, I thought I hadn’t seen it. On second watch I still don’t understand why this…
